This study is a randomized controlled trial that tests the effectiveness of cognitive behavior therapy (CBT) for insomnia with comorbid depression in youth aged 12 through 19 who have recently begun selective serotonin re-uptake inhibitor (SSRI) antidepressants.

 CBT is compared with a control condition of sleep hygiene education.

